- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper uses information theoretic tools to achieve optimal computation strategies in the case of random measurements. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper studies optimal block computation strategies for computing Boolean functions. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper considers collocated wireless sensor networks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is possible because the paper deals with networks of sensors and their communication. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is possible because the paper uses lower bounds from communication complexity theory.
